text.section:
The receiver of a nursing home or community program shall:
Give each individual and interested parties with respect to each individual notice of the receivership;
Preserve all property of and records that relate to an individual and are in the custody of the receiver or the owner or operating entity;
If an individual is to be discharged or transferred:
Explain to the individual or guardian of the individual the alternative placements that are available;
Help the individual or guardian of the individual to find an alternative placement;
Give information about the alternative placement chosen;
Transport the individual to the alternative placement; and
Transfer all property of and records on the individual, including all necessary medical information, to the individual or the alternative placement.
